FBIS3-39307 "drweu031_q_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-031 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Feb 1994 TURKEY France To Provide $50 Million in Development Loans TA1402152594 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1440 GMT 14 Feb 94 TA1402152594 Ankara ANATOLIA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Ankara, Feb 14 (A.A) -- France will extend 302.2 million Francs (approximately 51-million dollar) credit to Turkey in a bid to finance regions which have priority for development, it was reported on Monday [14 February]. Turkey and France ratified a protocol on the issue foreseeing France's financial support to Turkey. Under the protocol which was published in today's OFFICIAL GAZETTE, the credit will be used in Balikesir and Mersin's third water purification systems, electrification of Divrigi-Iskenderun railway line, in Alanya's small churn water purification system and in Istanbul's organized leather industry projects. The credit will provide a financial support to purchase French-origin items.
